# FunCode Design System — derive or update, never bespoke

Authority lives on the Chain. Before creating or editing any UI under `web/`, retrieve it — do not work from memory:

```bash
pb get DEC-11   # the design-system decision (code = SSOT, Chain = governance)
pb get STD-1    # design tokens (Tailwind v4 @theme, semantic-by-role)
pb get STD-2    # icon standard (unplugin-icons + Lucide via ~icons/lucide/*)
pb get STD-3    # atom contract (Svelte 5 + svelte/elements wrapper pattern)
pb get BR-2     # the rule below
pb get ROL-2    # Product Design — owns the system
```

## The rule (BR-2)

**Derive from the design system, or update it with Product Design (ROL-2). Never bespoke.**

- **Reuse** the atoms exported from `web/src/lib/components/ui/` (Icon, Button, Badge, Card, Accordion, Avatar, Marquee, Testimonial, AudienceChip, …) and the `@theme` tokens in `web/src/routes/layout.css`.
- **Semantic surfaces:** use `bg-surface`, `bg-surface-muted`, `border-border`, `text-muted` — never Tailwind `neutral-*` palette classes.
- **Icons:** `import IconX from '~icons/lucide/<name>'`; size/color via Tailwind + `currentColor`. Never inline `<svg>`, never `lucide-svelte` or runtime `@iconify/svelte`.
- **Colors/spacing/radius/shadow:** use tokens (`bg-accent`, `text-ink`, `rounded-card`, …). Never hardcode hex or arbitrary `[...]` values for themed properties.
- **Buttons:** compose the `Button` atom, never a re-styled raw `<button>`.

## When the system lacks something

Do **not** invent a one-off because you want to or assume you need it (wanting to build is not authorization — `BR-1`). Instead **update the system**:

1. Add/extend the token, atom, or standard in `web/` **and** capture the change on the Chain under Product Design (`ROL-2`) — update the relevant `STD` / `DEC`.
2. Keep code and Chain in sync.

## Enforcement

Run before finishing UI work — these fail on bespoke UI:

```bash
cd web && npm run lint   # includes the design-system guard (lint:ds)
```

The guard (`web/scripts/check-design-system.mjs`) blocks hardcoded hex/rgb, arbitrary themed values, inline `<svg>`, raw `<button>`, `neutral-*` palette classes, and forbidden icon imports. Tier 1 eval: `cd web && npm run eval:ds` (PAT-11). Also runs in CI.
